Pablo Zabaleta reckons Sergio Aguero can become Manchester City's first Ballon d'Or winner - but only if he can stay injury free.

The Argentina striker hit 19 goals in 20 games this season before suffering a knee ligament injury in December - the latest in a long line of setbacks.

And his international and club team-mate thinks that if he can repeat the form but not the setbacks he could be crowned the best footballer on the planet.

